item.title: What do you want to be?
item.dc:creator: @Ollie Ollie
item.description:
@Ollie wrote:

Niall:

I don’t know what I want to do, it’s just a shame the only 2 plausible trades I’d consider(electrician and plumber) have always had a very long waiting list.

Get an apprentership! And there is a national shortage of plumbers and electricians so you should (cross-fingers) get a job fairly fast. Just go down to the local job centre, but be prepared to work for little money in the first years, because effectively your employer is teaching you and paying you a wage at the same time.

I would say be an electrician out of the two, because i wouldnt like to get wet on the job, and have to fix peoples drains/sinks :p.
